sense.name: Resolve into factors via mathematical operation.
sense.examples: A quantum computer can factor the number 15. Factor out the problem before proceeding to the next step.

sense.name: (Cause to) be (considered) a part or property of something, possibly with the intent of setting it aside or apart.
sense.commentary: Includes: FACTOR OUT, FACTOR IN, FACTOR INTO
sense.examples: Many things factor into a company's profitability. The adjustment probably didn't factor out all of the wide-ranging surge in defense orders. You must factor in the recent developments in your analysis. Lower feed prices may help animals eat more cheaply, but humans have to factor in an expensive middleman: the processor.

sense.name: FACTOR ANALYZE: perform factor analysis, as in statistics.
sense.examples: Factor analyze the data. Sometime it's difficult to get students to factor analyze.
